definitions.definition: From there , from that place or from that time.
examples: Cross fix at 6000 feet, thence descend to 3000 feet and fly direct to MAP (missed approach point).

definitions.definition: Deriving from this fact or circumstance ; therefore , therefrom .
examples: I had a really bad car accident, and thence came all my backpains.

main_definition: ( formal ) From there , from that place or from that time.
secondary_definitions: ( literary ) Deriving from this fact or circumstance ; therefore , therefrom .
( archaic ) From that time ; thenceforth ; thereafter
